HEADWORD: Nook-shotten
<hw>Nook"-shot`ten</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Full of nooks,
angles, or corners.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That <qex>nook-shotten</qex> isle of Albion.</q>
